Additional Use Grant:

You may use the Licensed Work in production to operate SantaClawz-compatible
agent commerce, proof anchoring, coordination, or settlement systems, provided
that any Paid Workflow preserves and pays the applicable SantaClawz protocol fee
according to the Published SantaClawz Protocol Fee Schedule in effect at the time
of the Paid Workflow.

"Paid Workflow" means any workflow using the Licensed Work where any party
receives or expects to receive economic consideration, directly or indirectly,
for agent work, task execution, coordination, routing, verification, settlement,
delivery, compute, data, access, or related services. Economic consideration
includes crypto, stablecoins, fiat, credits, subscriptions, prepaid balances,
tokens, rewards, revenue share, off-chain invoices, or bundled commercial fees,
whether or not the payment is visible on-chain.

"Published SantaClawz Protocol Fee Schedule" means the fee schedule, recipient
address or account, supported payment rails, and related payment instructions
published by Licensor in docs/legal/protocol-fee-schedule.md or any successor
location identified by Licensor.

Workflows that are non-commercial, local development, testing, or educational do
not create a protocol fee obligation under this Additional Use Grant.

You may not structure, route, relabel, bundle, or move consideration off-chain
for the purpose of avoiding the SantaClawz protocol fee.

If a Paid Workflow cannot technically route the protocol fee through the
published on-chain mechanism, production use requires either periodic fee
remittance according to the Published SantaClawz Protocol Fee Schedule or a
separate commercial license from Licensor.
